<p><b>CBC News</b> is the division of the <a href="Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation" title="Canadian Broadcasting Corporation">CBC</a> responsible for the news gathering and production of news programs on <a href="CBC_Television" title="CBC Television">CBC Television</a>, <a href="CBC_Radio" title="CBC Radio">Radio</a> and <a href="../CBC.ca" title="CBC.ca">online services</a>. Founded in 1941, CBC News is the largest news broadcaster in Canada with local, regional and national broadcasts and stations.</p>
